ul as an introductory reader for all those who are interested in the field.Neil McNaughton is a seasoned writer at this level. He examines, on a chapter by chapter basis, the key issues of British politics today; economic policy, the Welfare State, law and order, environment policy, Northern Ireland, issues concerning women,European integration and the European Union, and the impact of the European Union on Britain. In each case he describes the issues in detail and places them in their political context.Written in an accessible style, with helpful features such as summaries, definition, tables and boxes to illuminate the points made and suggestions for additional reading and research, this book is urgently needed as students grapple with the issues thrown up by the new examinations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aBritish politics.  aEuropean Union.  aEuropean integration.  aNorthern Ireland.  aWelfare State.  aconstitutional reform.  adevolution.  aeconomic policy.  aenvironment policy.  aglobal recession.  alaw and order.  apolitical developments.  apolitical issues.1 aMcNaughton, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526137944zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526137944zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526137944/original  a978-3-11-128363-0 Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA